  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2019-05-09",
    "date": "2020-11-09T17:42:32Z",
    "text": "Closing the Loophole on Interstate Firearm Sales Act\n\nThis bill generally prohibits a licensed importer, manufacturer, dealer, or collector (transferor) from selling or delivering a rifle or shotgun to an out-of-state resident (transferee). Specifically, the bill removes an exception under current law that allows a transferee to obtain a rifle or shotgun from a transferor in another state, provided that (1) the transferee and transferor meet in person to accomplish the transfer; and (2) the sale, delivery, and receipt of the firearm comply with the laws of both states."
  },
